title: Weaver's Thesis Book (France), 1893
inscribed:
Inside cover: Théodore Bon, 1893, Lyon; 
Below: Ce livre provenant de la bibliotheque de M.F. Peyot, ancien professeur de Théorie de Tissage, parait être ecrit de la main même de M. Peyot. Il est consacré entierement a l'etude des gazes
dimensions:
H x W: 33 × 26 cm (13 in. × 10 1/4 in.)
160 pages
description: Oblong book, bound in dark green leather, with flap and metal clasp, contains 150 numbered pages of descriptions, analysis, weave diagrams and samples of gauzes, with mises-en-carte for many. 91 small samples.

tombstone.epitaph:
